            <title>[SEC-3020] HttpServletRequest.isUserInRole(&quot;ROLE_&lt;anything&gt;&quot;) returns false with defaults</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-3020</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just trying to upgrade from Spring Security 3.1 to 4.0.1 and have discovered a breaking change in the behaviour of request.isUserInRole().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Spring 3.1 the following was returning true and now returns false:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;request.isUserInRole(&quot;ROLE_REMEMBER_ME&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Spring 4.0.1 I had to change it to the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;request.isUserInRole(&quot;REMEMBER_ME&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
